I think if <i>prodigal_erik</i> is worried about autovivification then perhaps locking the keys might be a good idea?...<p><pre><code>  use 5.016;
  use warnings;
  use Hash::Util &#x27;lock_keys&#x27;;

  my %a = (B => 100);  # B but no A defined
  lock_keys %a;

  my $x = &#x27;A&#x27;;
  ++$a{$x};
</code></pre>
Above now throws an error on the last line - <i>Attempt to access disallowed key &#x27;A&#x27; in a restricted hash...</i><p>Alternatively autovivification can be switched off - <a href"https://metacpan.org/pod/autovivificatio" rel"nofollo">https://metacpan.org/pod/autovivification</a>
